{"parentUuid":"4d5b1d13-e9c7-4a20-92ea-2d22dab0ee42","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\johnm\\iskrib_v3","sessionId":"7b6de7bc-fd78-466f-abf0-ee2dadbc4f03","version":"2.1.50","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"jazzy-sprouting-candle","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01A8U67C6qcLYMJbFo7vefS1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The warning is about **line 21** — the `fb:app_id` meta tag:\n\n```html\n<meta id=\"seo-fb-app-id\" property=\"fb:app_id\" content=\"%VITE_FB_APP_ID%\" />\n```\n\nVite replaces `%VITE_*%` placeholders in `index.html` at build time, but `VITE_FB_APP_ID` isn't defined in your `.env` file, so it stays as the literal string.\n\n**Two options:**\n\n1. **If you have a Facebook App ID** — add it to your `.env` file:\n   ```\n   VITE_FB_APP_ID=your_facebook_app_id_here\n   ```\n\n2. **If you don't need it** — just remove line 21 from `client/index.html`. The `fb:app_id` tag is only needed if you want Facebook Open Graph analytics tied to a specific Facebook app. It's not required for OG sharing to work.\n\nWant me to remove it, or do you have an app ID to add?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1352,"cache_read_input_tokens":23619,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1352},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CYT2LCYMgRcAx6GWwyZ5e","type":"assistant","uuid":"f2720d31-b9b9-416b-9ad6-dd70f9811036","timestamp":"2026-02-24T14:07:12.141Z"}
