{"parentUuid":"3d8c8676-6abb-4fa3-9665-c07fa154708c","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\johnm\\iskrib_v3","sessionId":"7b6de7bc-fd78-466f-abf0-ee2dadbc4f03","version":"2.1.50","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"jazzy-sprouting-candle","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01R1fYELmKAd4tAtnJ6uc8CR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `fb:app_id` meta tag links your site's shared content to a Facebook App, which gives you:\n\n1. **Facebook Sharing Insights** — Access analytics in the Facebook Developer dashboard showing how often your links are shared, clicked, and engaged with on Facebook\n2. **Moderation** — Ability to moderate comments on shared links (if using the Facebook Comments plugin)\n3. **Attribution** — Shared links get associated with your app, which can slightly improve how Facebook caches/displays your previews\n\n**Realistically though**, for most sites it's low value. OG sharing (title, image, description previews) works fine without it. The main benefit is the share analytics.\n\nIf you're not actively using a Facebook App for iskrib, I'd just remove the line to clean up the warning. You can always add it back later if needed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13,"cache_read_input_tokens":25225,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CYT2NxFTZtmneq7BvJuzf","type":"assistant","uuid":"7c1a5062-eae0-4f5a-a730-2f533b95c6be","timestamp":"2026-02-24T14:07:50.241Z"}
